nasty in Florida, perhaps as a sort of placeholder until the couple move in=
to the White House in 2028. =E2=80=9CShe took it on the chin like DeSantis,=
=E2=80=9D said one Florida pollster. =E2=80=9CHer agenda is tied to Ron=E2=
=80=99s culture wars, but she=E2=80=99s polling ahead of Matt Gaetz, Wilton=
 Simpson, and Ashley Moody by double digits. I wouldn=E2=80=99t be surprise=
d if she=E2=80=99s a candidate one day. She wins a four- or five-way race w=
here you don=E2=80=99t have to have 50 percent.=E2=80=9D

There are hard choices to be made for the DeSantii, for whom being in offic=
e has become a lifestyle. DeSantis had a net worth of $300,000 when he was =
elected
governor; now he has a $300,000 golf simulator in the governor=E2=80=99s ma=
nsion and a lot more money in the bank, thanks to sales of his bestselling =
2023 autobiography. He uses the state-owned, $15 million Cessna Citation so=
 often that local reporters have dubbed it =E2=80=9CAir DeSantis.=E2=80=9D =
